I was starting to worry
that you wouldn't crack it.

154
00:14:37.626 --> 00:14:40.379 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We used to use that cipher
all the time

155
00:14:40.462 --> 00:14:42.506 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
when we passed notes in class.

156
00:14:47.553 --> 00:14:49.930 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Doesn't it take you back?

157
00:14:51.974 --> 00:14:54.518 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Badmouthing the professors.</i>

158
00:14:54.602 --> 00:14:56.270 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Asking about our nemesis.</i>

159
00:14:56.353 --> 00:14:57.855 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Our favorite records.</i>

160
00:14:58.939 --> 00:15:01.150 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yours was Blue Oyster Cult,

161
00:15:01.233 --> 00:15:03.444 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and mine was Thin Lizzy.

162
00:15:04.612 --> 00:15:06.822 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Keith] <i>Yours was Kate Bush.</i>

163
00:15:09.783 --> 00:15:11.243 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hurry over.

164
00:15:11.327 --> 00:15:14.371 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Gilbert] <i>This place</i>
<i>has seen better days,</i>

165
00:15:14.455 --> 00:15:17.207 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>but things are</i>
<i>as they were back then.</i>

166
00:15:19.251 --> 00:15:22.129 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He said that <i>he </i>would
bring all this to an end.

167
00:15:22.212 --> 00:15:24.131 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And those were
his exact words to you?

168
00:15:24.214 --> 00:15:25.132 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah.

169
00:15:25.215 --> 00:15:27.384 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If he's going
to the scene of the crime,

170
00:15:27.468 --> 00:15:29.887 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that's the murder scene
up there in the mountains.

171
00:15:29.970 --> 00:15:31.138 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But you're forgetting something.

172
00:15:31.221 --> 00:15:33.057 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's where her body
was dumped,

173
00:15:33.140 --> 00:15:34.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
not where she was killed.

174
00:15:34.433 --> 00:15:37.102 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The place where Erika
was actually murdered was...

175
00:15:39.939 --> 00:15:42.107 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Tell me one thing.

176
00:15:42.191 --> 00:15:43.943 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>What?</i>

177
00:15:44.026 --> 00:15:47.237 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You couldn't have carried it out
on your own authority.

178
00:15:47.321 --> 00:15:48.948 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Tell me who ordered it.

179
00:15:49.031 --> 00:15:52.076 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Hmm? Oh, you mean the attack?</i>

180
00:15:52.159 --> 00:15:55.329 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There's a simple explanation.

181
00:15:55.412 --> 00:15:57.373 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jaula Blanca's main product

182
00:15:57.456 --> 00:16:00.376 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
was the living weapons
called Reggies.

183
00:16:00.459 --> 00:16:01.794 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The king and military

184
00:16:01.877 --> 00:16:04.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
couldn't care less
about resurrecting gods.

185
00:16:04.755 --> 00:16:06.966 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Success was the last thing
they wanted.

186
00:16:10.010 --> 00:16:12.888 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And I'll let you in
on one other detail.

187
00:16:12.972 --> 00:16:16.308 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The one who proposed and
led the attack on the Institute

188
00:16:16.392 --> 00:16:17.893 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
was none other than myself.

189
00:16:19.853 --> 00:16:24.191 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I instructed Minatsuki
to kill Dr. Kazama.

190
00:16:24.274 --> 00:16:28.070 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[scoffs]
Children are strange things.

191
00:16:28.153 --> 00:16:30.280 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They'll believe
anything you tell them,

192
00:16:30.364 --> 00:16:33.075 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>as long as it's</i>
<i>what they want to hear.</i>

193
00:16:39.540 --> 00:16:43.252 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Question-- Why weren't you
controlled by him?

194
00:16:43.335 --> 00:16:46.797 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, you're referring
to the ability

195
00:16:46.880 --> 00:16:49.174 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in Minatsuki's right eye?

196
00:16:49.258 --> 00:16:54.638 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[laughs] <i>You know why,</i>
<i>and yet you're asking anyway.</i>

197
00:16:54.722 --> 00:16:57.433 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's because you were
controlling him, right?

198
00:16:57.516 --> 00:16:59.393 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

199
00:17:02.062 --> 00:17:04.481 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When it comes
to childhood beliefs,

200
00:17:04.565 --> 00:17:07.401 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
unless the child
sees irrefutable proof

201
00:17:07.484 --> 00:17:11.113 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
with its own eyes,
they will never fade.

202
00:17:11.196 --> 00:17:13.115 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's a sort of hypnosis,
you see.

203
00:17:13.198 --> 00:17:18.412 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It was quite the clumsy lie,
yet he still believed it.

204
00:17:18.495 --> 00:17:21.248 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Even now, he believes
that if he kills Koku

205
00:17:21.331 --> 00:17:23.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
in the manner
set out in the inscription,

206
00:17:23.417 --> 00:17:27.671 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
he'll rule over a new world
as its invincible king.

207
00:17:28.756 --> 00:17:30.132 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>How many?</i>

208
00:17:30.215 --> 00:17:33.510 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>How many lives</i>
<i>will you toy with</i>

209
00:17:33.594 --> 00:17:35.554 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>before you're satisfied?</i>

210
00:17:40.976 --> 00:17:42.853 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Surely you see it now.

211
00:17:42.936 --> 00:17:46.315 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
These cravings of mine
will never be satisfied.

212
00:17:48.817 --> 00:17:53.072 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Truth is, I have to kill
in order to survive.

213
00:17:56.241 --> 00:18:00.329 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But, you know, Keith, if you
gave it an iota of thought,

214
00:18:00.412 --> 00:18:04.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you'd see that we're the same.
Don't you agree?

215
00:18:06.043 --> 00:18:10.130 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
My impulse to kill
and yours to study,

216
00:18:10.214 --> 00:18:15.427 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we're the same in that neither
one of us can control ourselves.

217
00:18:15.511 --> 00:18:19.598 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's a trait
that's common to all Flicks.

218
00:18:19.681 --> 00:18:24.061 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If I recall, Erika wasn't able
to control her emotions either,

219
00:18:24.144 --> 00:18:25.395 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and so I...

220
00:18:29.316 --> 00:18:31.693 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

221
00:18:31.777 --> 00:18:35.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Since we both belong
to such cursed bloodlines,

222
00:18:35.572 --> 00:18:38.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
what do you say
we put an end to this?

223
00:19:14.736 --> 00:19:16.738 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[woman vocalizing]

224
00:19:31.461 --> 00:19:34.047 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In this place,
the glyph for "black"

225
00:19:34.131 --> 00:19:37.843 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
is repeatedly used
as a synonym for "perfect."

226
00:19:37.926 --> 00:19:42.347 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you know
how one makes the color black?

227
00:19:42.431 --> 00:19:45.934 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You have to mix all
of the other colors together.

228
00:19:47.603 --> 00:19:51.690 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's the reason black stands
apart from the other colors.

229
00:19:51.773 --> 00:19:56.236 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>It's the perfect color,</i>
<i>one fit for a king.</i>

230
00:20:00.616 --> 00:20:02.618 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>You don't know, do you?</i>

231
00:20:02.701 --> 00:20:07.122 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You don't have the slightest
idea why I'm doing this.

232
00:20:08.624 --> 00:20:10.542 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I listened to you.

233
00:20:10.626 --> 00:20:14.129 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I heard your voices</i>
<i>in the distance</i>

234
00:20:14.213 --> 00:20:15.797 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>as I listened</i>
<i>through the window.</i>

235
00:20:15.881 --> 00:20:17.758 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[children chattering]

236
00:20:17.841 --> 00:20:21.553 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>To pass the time, I imagined</i>
<i>what the rest of you were like.</i>

237
00:20:21.637 --> 00:20:26.683 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Until Izanami came,</i>
<i>I'd been alone my entire life.</i>

238
00:20:26.767 --> 00:20:29.061 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>More than anything,</i>
<i>I wanted to know</i>

239
00:20:29.144 --> 00:20:31.855 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>why I was the only one</i>
<i>kept isolated.</i>

240
00:20:36.068 --> 00:20:38.237 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And on that bloody night,

241
00:20:38.320 --> 00:20:40.739 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
he explained everything to me.

242
00:20:40.822 --> 00:20:43.325 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I was created and kept alive</i>

243
00:20:43.408 --> 00:20:45.744 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>to be used as spare parts</i>
<i>for Koku.</i>

244
00:20:45.827 --> 00:20:49.206 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>My destiny was that I'd</i>
<i>be carved up as we grew</i>

245
00:20:49.289 --> 00:20:53.001 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and eventually put down</i>
<i>like a stray dog.</i>

246
00:20:53.085 --> 00:20:55.045 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>That's why</i>
<i>there isn't any record</i>

247
00:20:55.128 --> 00:20:57.256 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>of my existence</i>
<i>in the inscription.</i>

248
00:20:57.339 --> 00:21:02.177 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Until then, I was
nothing more than a phantom.

249
00:21:06.223 --> 00:21:09.142 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He was the one and only Reggie

250
00:21:09.226 --> 00:21:11.478 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
who was successfully stabilized
through treatment

251
00:21:11.561 --> 00:21:14.856 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and showed no signs of one day
rejecting Koku's eye.

252
00:21:15.941 --> 00:21:17.985 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He was kept in strict isolation,

253
00:21:18.068 --> 00:21:19.319 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
which is only natural,

254
00:21:19.403 --> 00:21:21.822 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
considering that if
the military learned of him,

255
00:21:21.905 --> 00:21:23.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
he'd be eliminated.

256
00:21:24.992 --> 00:21:28.787 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Keith] He's the last hope
for stabilizing the Reggies.

257
00:21:29.997 --> 00:21:31.832 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I get it now.

258
00:21:31.915 --> 00:21:37.087 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The real target of that attack
was Minatsuki, wasn't it?

259
00:21:39.464 --> 00:21:41.967 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Minatsuki]
<i>I didn't want to believe it.</i>

260
00:21:42.050 --> 00:21:45.429 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I fought against the inscription
with all I had,

261
00:21:45.512 --> 00:21:47.931 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but it was hopeless.

262
00:21:51.310 --> 00:21:53.979 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The first time
I laid my eyes on his eye,

263
00:21:54.062 --> 00:21:56.565 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
it convinced me it was all true,

264
00:21:56.648 --> 00:21:58.859 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and so I swore to myself,

265
00:21:58.942 --> 00:22:02.070 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>whatever it took,</i>

266
00:22:02.154 --> 00:22:04.197 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'd steal everything from him...

267
00:22:05.240 --> 00:22:07.784 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
using my own two hands.

268
00:22:08.910 --> 00:22:09.911 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You can't.

269
00:22:16.918 --> 00:22:19.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I know that Koku
will never lose,

270
00:22:19.629 --> 00:22:23.717 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so there's absolutely nothing
you can steal from him.

271
00:22:25.761 --> 00:22:27.679 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You still don't seem to get it.

272
00:22:29.681 --> 00:22:32.017 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasping]

273
00:22:33.101 --> 00:22:34.019 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Koku gasps]

274
00:22:35.353 --> 00:22:36.772 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Can't you see?

275
00:22:36.855 --> 00:22:38.398 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're all playing out our roles

276
00:22:38.482 --> 00:22:41.068 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
precisely as it's written
in this inscription.

277
00:22:41.151 --> 00:22:43.487 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Life, death,
and everything in between,

278
00:22:43.570 --> 00:22:46.281 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
there's no fighting against it,
no matter what you do.

279
00:22:47.449 --> 00:22:49.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We are nothing more
than bit players

280
00:22:49.493 --> 00:22:50.952 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in a repeating story,

281
00:22:51.036 --> 00:22:55.415 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
which is why
you're going to die here

282
00:22:55.499 --> 00:22:57.334 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
along with Koku.

283
00:22:57.417 --> 00:23:00.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yuna!

284
00:23:02.422 --> 00:23:08.136 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Someday I'll be gone ♪</i>

285
00:23:10.180 --> 00:23:16.394 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>♪ There's somewhere</i>
<i>That we belong ♪</i>

286
00:23:18.063 --> 00:23:22.317 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>♪ And God</i>
<i>Has never played his role ♪</i>

287
00:23:22.400 --> 00:23:26.655 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>♪ 'Cause I'm the one</i>
<i>Who saves my soul ♪</i>

288
00:23:26.738 --> 00:23:32.285 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>♪ It's a perfect world</i>
<i>We're longing for ♪</i>

289
00:23:32.369 --> 00:23:34.788 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>♪ So long ♪</i>

290
00:24:01.481 --> 00:24:03.608 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Cursing shadows ♪</i>

291
00:24:03.692 --> 00:24:05.193 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Hunt and gather ♪</i>

292
00:24:05.277 --> 00:24:09.364 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>♪ In the city of no answer ♪</i>

293
00:24:09.447 --> 00:24:13.493 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>♪ As we follow</i>
<i>Endless questions ♪</i>

294
00:24:13.577 --> 00:24:17.706 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>♪ Hands up</i>
<i>In the same reflection ♪</i>

295
00:24:17.789 --> 00:24:19.749 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>♪ Sometimes we try to feel ♪</i>

296
00:24:19.833 --> 00:24:24.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>♪ How things just used to be</i>
